criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Female between 18 and 28 years;

          -  BMI below 30;

          -  Practicing recreational physical activity at least three times a week without training
             at a competitive level;

          -  Exhibiting shoulder joint, elbow and non-dominant hand integrity;

          -  Do not having a history of osteo-myoarticular injuries in the assessed limb in the
             last 6 months.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Does not run the tests properly;

          -  Be allergic to tape test;

          -  Does not attend all assessments.
